The paper deals with the design of locally decodable codes in the presence of resource constraints, specifically in settings where the channel is slightly more constrained than the encoder/decoder with respect to some resource. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the areas of cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), complexity theory (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
